df_carvalo_export <- read.csv("../data/CognitiveTutorData2011-12_CarvalhoExport.csv")
df_carvalo_export_labels <- read.csv("../data/CognitiveTutorData2011-12_CarvalhoExport_Labels.csv")
df_student_session_info_merged_reliability_long <- read.csv("../data_EDM_25/df_student_session_info_merged_reliability_long.csv")
df_summary <- df_student_session_info_merged_reliability_long %>% 
  group_by(actual_student_id) %>%
  summarise(
    avg_delayed_start = mean(avg_delayed_start), 
    avg_relative_delayed_start = mean(avg_relative_delayed_start), 
    avg_early_stop = mean(avg_early_stop),
    avg_relative_early_stop = mean(avg_relative_early_stop),
    avg_student_session_idel_time_2 = mean(avg_student_session_idel_time_2),
    avg_relative_idel_session_time_2 = mean(avg_relative_idel_session_time_2),
    avg_student_session_length_mins = mean(avg_student_session_length_mins),
    avg_relative_student_session_length_mins = mean(avg_relative_student_session_length_mins),
    total_time_on_task = mean(total_time_on_task),
    time_usage_ratio = mean(time_usage_ratio),
    relative_time_usage_ratio = mean(relative_time_usage_ratio),
    attendance=mean(attendance),
    latent_gaming_estimate = mean(latent_gaming_estimate)
  )
df_predictive_validity_ <- left_join(df_summary, 
                                    df_carvalo_export %>% 
                                      select(actual_student_id, finalmath, priorfinalgrade, pssa2011math_scaledscore, pssa2012math_scalescore), 
                                    by=c("actual_student_id")) %>% 
  filter(priorfinalgrade < 999 & finalmath < 999)
# print(t(summary(df_predictive_validity_)))
# lapply(df_predictive_validity_, function(x){
#   sd(na.omit(x))
# })
df_predictive_validity <- df_predictive_validity_ %>% 
  mutate(
    avg_delayed_start = scale(avg_delayed_start),
    avg_relative_delayed_start = scale(avg_relative_delayed_start),
    avg_early_stop = scale(avg_early_stop),
    avg_relative_early_stop = scale(avg_relative_early_stop),
    avg_student_session_idel_time_2 = scale(avg_student_session_idel_time_2),
    avg_relative_idel_session_time_2 = scale(avg_relative_idel_session_time_2),
    avg_student_session_length_mins = scale(avg_student_session_length_mins),
    avg_relative_student_session_length_mins = scale(avg_relative_student_session_length_mins),
    total_time_on_task = scale(total_time_on_task),
    time_usage_ratio = scale(time_usage_ratio),
    relative_time_usage_ratio = scale(relative_time_usage_ratio),
    attendance = scale(attendance),
    latent_gaming_estimate = scale(latent_gaming_estimate),
    finalmath = scale(finalmath),
    priorfinalgrade = scale(priorfinalgrade)
  ) %>% 
  subset((finalmath > -3 & finalmath < 3) & (priorfinalgrade > -3 & priorfinalgrade < 3))

library(tibble)

data_selected <- df_predictive_validity %>% dplyr::select(-c(actual_student_id, pssa2011math_scaledscore, pssa2012math_scalescore))
# Calculate correlation and p-values
features_list <- c("avg_delayed_start", "avg_relative_delayed_start", "avg_early_stop", "avg_relative_early_stop", "avg_student_session_idel_time_2", 
                   "avg_relative_idel_session_time_2", "avg_student_session_length_mins", "avg_relative_student_session_length_mins", "total_time_on_task", 
                   "time_usage_ratio", "relative_time_usage_ratio", "attendance", "latent_gaming_estimate", "finalmath", "priorfinalgrade")
cor_matrix <- rcorr(as.matrix(data_selected))
correlations <- cor_matrix$r
colnames(correlations) <- features_list
rownames(correlations) <- features_list

p_values_vector <- as.vector(cor_matrix$P)
adjusted_p_values_vector <- p.adjust(p_values_vector, method = "BH")
# adjusted p_values with Benjamin Hochberg correction. 
p_values <- matrix(adjusted_p_values_vector, nrow = nrow(cor_matrix$P), ncol = ncol(cor_matrix$P))

colnames(p_values) <- features_list
rownames(p_values) <- features_list

# Convert to long format
cor_long <- as.data.frame(correlations) %>%
  rownames_to_column(var = "Var1") %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = -Var1, names_to = "Var2", values_to = "Correlation")

p_long <- as.data.frame(p_values) %>%
  rownames_to_column(var = "Var1") %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = -Var1, names_to = "Var2", values_to = "P_Value")

# Merge and add significance
cor_p_long <- merge(cor_long, p_long, by = c("Var1", "Var2"))
cor_p_long$Significance <- ifelse(cor_p_long$P_Value < 0.001, '***',
                                  ifelse(cor_p_long$P_Value < 0.01, '**',
                                         ifelse(cor_p_long$P_Value < 0.05, '*', '')))

# ggplot(cor_p_long, aes(Var2, Var1, fill = Correlation)) +
#   geom_tile() +
#   geom_text(aes(label = sprintf("%.2f", Correlation)), color = "black") +

# Define the desired order for features
features_list_ordered <- c("avg_delayed_start", "avg_relative_delayed_start", "avg_student_session_length_mins", "avg_relative_student_session_length_mins", 
                           "avg_early_stop", "avg_relative_early_stop", "avg_student_session_idel_time_2", "avg_relative_idel_session_time_2", 
                           "time_usage_ratio", "relative_time_usage_ratio", "total_time_on_task", "attendance", "latent_gaming_estimate", 
                           "finalmath", "priorfinalgrade")

# Filter correlations where absolute value > 0.7
cor_p_long <- cor_p_long %>%
  filter(abs(Correlation) > 0.7)

# Reorder Var1 and Var2 in cor_p_long according to features_list_ordered
cor_p_long$Var1 <- factor(cor_p_long$Var1, levels = rev(features_list_ordered))
cor_p_long$Var2 <- factor(cor_p_long$Var2, levels = features_list_ordered)

# Plot the heatmap with ggplot2
cor_plot <- ggplot(cor_p_long, aes(x = Var2, y = Var1, fill = Correlation)) +
  geom_tile() +
  geom_text(aes(label = sprintf("%.2f", Correlation)), color = "#000000", size=5) +
  geom_text(aes(label = Significance, y = as.numeric(Var1) - 0.4), color = "#000000", size = 5) +  # Adjusted size for significance labels
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "#f8766d", high = "#00ba38", mid = "#ebebeb", midpoint = 0, limit = c(-1, 1)) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 28, hjust = 1, size = 19),  # Custom size for axis text
        axis.text.y = element_text(angle = 0, vjust = 0.5, size = 19),  # Custom size for axis text
        axis.title = element_blank(),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 16),  # Custom size for legend text
        legend.title = element_text(size = 16),  # Custom size for legend title
        plot.title = element_text(size = 19),  # Custom size for plot title
        text = element_text(size = 19)) +  # Default text size for all text elements
  labs(x = NULL, y = NULL)  # Remove axis labels
